        "message": "Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1\n\nJonathan,\n\nWe have made the oom changes and tested with OOM locally, see linked Gerrit reviews that are on the same topic :\n\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/103790\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/aaf/sms/+/103788\n\n\nWe can make the changes to the local repo helm charts (we just use an init container to chmod the NFS mount, which is the recommended k8s way) but what are their purpose ? it looks like a local way to deploy with helm and it will duplicate code and effort.\n\nI tested your changes  (patchset 10) on my local oom setup but\nthe bootstrap script executes but fails at several places :\n\n Cassandra responded\n cassandra responsive\n /opt/app/aaf/cass_init/cmd.sh: line 100: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n /opt/app/aaf/cass_init/cmd.sh: line 104: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n install\n Initializing Cassandra DB\n Docker Installed Basic Cassandra on aaf.cass.  Executing the following \n NOTE: This creator provided is only a Single Instance. For more complex Cassandra, create  independently\n\n cd /opt/app/aaf/cass_init\n cqlsh -f keyspace.cql\n /opt/app/aaf/cass_init/cmd.sh: line 113: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n keyspace installed\n cqlsh -f init.cql\n /opt/app/aaf/cass_init/cmd.sh: line 116: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n data initialized\n\n The following will give you a temporary identity with which to start working, or emergency\n cqlsh -f temp_identity.cql\n initialized\n prep data for bootstrapping\n prep data\n push data to cassandra\n Tue Mar 24 10:24:08 CET 2020\n /opt/app/aaf/cass_init\n You are about to REPLACE the data in the DOCKER DB for the following tables:\n artifact config cred ns perm role user_role\n If you are VERY sure, type \"YES\": artifact\n restore.sh: line 39: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n config\n restore.sh: line 47: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n cred\n restore.sh: line 39: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n ns\n restore.sh: line 39: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n perm\n restore.sh: line 47: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n role\n user_role\n restore.sh: line 39: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n restore.sh: line 47: /usr/bin/cqlsh: No such file or directory\n #### Running artifact.dat Feed ####\n com.datastax.driver.core.exceptions.InvalidQueryException: Keyspace authz does not exist\n\tat   com.datastax.driver.core.exceptions.InvalidQueryException.copy(InvalidQueryException.java:49)\n\tat com.datastax.driver.core.DriverThrowables.propagateCause(DriverThrowables.java:35)\n\tat  com.datastax.driver.core.DefaultResultSetFuture.getUninterruptibly(DefaultResultSetFuture.java: 293)\n\tat com.datastax.driver.core.AbstractSession.execute(AbstractSession.java:58)\n\tat com.datastax.driver.core.AbstractSession.execute(AbstractSession.java:39)\n\tat org.onap.aaf.auth.batch.helpers.CQLBatch.execute(CQLBatch.java:75)\n\tat org.onap.aaf.auth.batch.helpers.CQLBatch.execute(CQLBatch.java:99)\n\tat org.onap.aaf.auth.batch.helpers.CQLBatchLoop.flush(CQLBatchLoop.java:98)\n\tat org.onap.aaf.auth.batch.update.Upload.run(Upload.java:130)\n\nthis is why we updated to\n\n/opt/cassandra/bin/cqlsh\n\nwhich is where we find the cqlsh tool in the container",
